  "text": "Also in Italy there are similar projects launched by the Italian Ministry of University and Regional Governments that implement augmented experiences. For example, Tell MeWhere project [CITATION_1] , designed by the University of Modena and Reggio Emilia, realizes a system to offer augmented experiences to visitors of the Enzo Ferrari Museum in Modena. Using smartphones and glass cameras, this system recognizes visitor gestures and provides car details so they can learn more about the luxury cars. Other projects, DICET and SMST, are launched in Italy in 2013, with the common aim to augment the experience of visitors with an increased interactivity and connectivity [CITATION_2] .",
